00:00:02.000 --> 00:00:09.200
Indian Creamy Chicken

00:00:09.200 --> 00:00:11.000
Serve : 4

00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:12.200
Ingredients :

00:00:12.200 --> 00:00:14.500
1 tbsp olive oil

00:00:14.500 --> 00:00:16.000
1 tbsp butter

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:18.500
1 onion, finely chopped

00:00:18.500 --> 00:00:20.500
2 garlic cloves, minced

00:00:20.500 --> 00:00:24.200
2 tsp fresh ginger, grated

00:00:24.200 --> 00:00:30.000
1 red chilli, deseeded and finely chopped

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:31.500
2 cardamom seeds

00:00:31.500 --> 00:00:36.500
1 tsp garam masala

00:00:36.500 --> 00:00:38.800
1 tsp ground turmeric

00:00:38.800 --> 00:00:40.800
1 tbsp flour

00:00:40.800 --> 00:00:45.000
400 ml (1½ cups) chicken stock

00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:49.500
125 ml (½ cup) single cream

00:00:49.500 --> 00:00:53.500
4 large chicken breasts, cut into small pieces

00:00:53.500 --> 00:00:56.000
Fresh coriander for garnish

00:00:56.000 --> 00:00:57.500
Directions :

00:00:57.500 --> 00:01:03.500
Heat the olive oil and ½ the butter in a large saucepan

00:01:03.500 --> 00:01:08.000
and sauté the onion over medium heat until soft and translucent.

00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:20.000
Add the garlic, ginger, chilli, cardamom, garam masala and turmeric and cook for 2 minutes.

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:23.800
Add the flour and cook for another minute.

00:01:23.800 --> 00:01:31.000
Add the chicken stock and single cream and stir constantly until the sauce thickens. 

00:01:31.000 --> 00:01:38.700
Put the lid on and leave simmering over low heat for 15 min.

00:01:38.700 --> 00:01:46.500
Meanwhile, melt the remaining butter, season the chicken with salt and pepper

00:01:46.500 --> 00:01:54.500
and cook until golden brown on the outside.

00:01:54.500 --> 00:02:03.500
Add the chicken to the saucepan, adjust the seasoning of the sauce and leave cooking for 15 minutes.

00:02:03.500 --> 00:02:11.500
Sprinkle some coriander on top and serve with rice.

